<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Welcomes U.N. Arms Embargo Resolution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- France said Wednesday that the
United Nations Security Council resolution adopted on Tuesday to
impose arms embargo on the Yugoslav Federation is fair and
balanced.
</P>
<P>
"We consider this text as a balanced project capable of
contributing to a political solution to the present crisis in
Kosovo," said French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Anne
Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
She said that the measures taken by the Security Council must
be regarded as means to seek a political solution to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
"The Security Council will consider the lifting of the embargo
as soon as the Yugoslav Federation has met the five conditions
clearly cited by the resolution and originating from the
declaration of the Contact Group on former Yugoslavia" made in
London last month, she added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
