<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, April 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA -- Eight natives in the southern Philippines died and 40
others were hospitalized after they ate a wild root crop in the
past three months, the Philippine News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The eight victims in Maguindanao province died after eating a
crop called "kayos" (wild yam) due to starvation brought about by
the El Nino phenomenon. (Philippines-Food Poisoning)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli inner Cabinet formally approved Wednesday
the United Nations Resolution 425 calling for Israeli unilateral
withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel has been fighting a war with anti-Israeli Hezbollah
(Party of God) forces since 1985 in the region which Isreal seized
in the 1967 Middle East War. (Israel-Lebanon-Withdrawal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- More than 20 people were injured Wednesday when a
helicopter crashed on a landmine while landing in the northern
province of Preah Vihear of Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
On board were more than 30 people, including diplomats and
journalists on their way to visit the Preah Vihear Temple, a
former Khmer Rouge stronghold near the border of Thailand.
(Cambodia-Helicopter)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Wednesday expressed its appreciation for the
decision of the European Union (EU) to resume political dialog
with Tehran, the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
EU foreign ministers on Tuesday decided to resume "critical
dialog" with Iran and called for promotion of bilateral ties.
(Iran-EU-Dialog)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Turkey and Pakistan reiterated their desire for
early return of peace and tranquillity in the war-torn Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also agreed to work together for the
promotion of intra-Afghan dialogue for a peaceful negotiated
settlement. (Pakistan-Turkey-Visit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
