<DOCNO> XIE19980402.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Underlines Importance of Educating Cadres (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The latest issue of the "Study on
Party Building" journal carries an important speech on the
education of leading cadres by the Communist Party of China (CPC)
General Secretary Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
In the speech, delivered by Jiang on December 22, 1997, the
Party leader gives top priority to the role of cadres in carrying
out various tasks of the country.
</P>
<P>
Cadres are a decisive factor in implementing the correct line
and policy, arousing the masses of people, and resolving problems
in the Party and the society, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the 21st century is a century in which the CPC will
lead the people to invigorate the Chinese nation in an all-round
way, Jiang said the Communist Party shoulders a great historical
responsibility, and the cadres, especially leading and
middle-ranking cadres, shoulder the great historical
responsibility.
</P>
<P>
Strict criterions must be adhered to, in order to fostering and
training young cadres and to help them become ideal successors of
the older generation, he says.
</P>
<P>
The on-job leading cadres at all levels are well-learned,
energetic and much younger, but they lag behind the veteran cadres
of the older generation in terms of political experience, the
ability to organize, and ideological style, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Some cadres have failed to stand the trial since the
country launched its current reform and opening-up drive in the
late 1970s, he says, urging cadres to learn lessons from the past
experience.
</P>
<P>
Jiang criticizes some cadres for their failure to study
theories assiduously, to ponder problems deeply, make
investigations and studies, and work hard and in a down-to-earth
way. And some of them have even been indulged in luxury life, he
adds.
</P>
<P>
He pledges to wipe out all these evil styles that would be
detrimental to the State and the people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980402.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Underlines Importance of Educating Cadres (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Meanwhile, in his speech, Jiang reiterates what he has said
repeatedly that leading cadres should be subjected to the serious
and strict demands and disciplines, management and supervision,
and, leading cadres should respect, retrospect and encourage
themselves.
</P>
<P>
The Party chief calls on cadres to give top priority to
studying, so as to improve their theoretic and knowledge level. He
proposes to launch a new wave of studying Marxism-Leninism and Mao
Zedong Thought.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also advises cadres to maintain a high uniformity with
the Party Central Leadership, seriously implement the principle of
democratic centralism, serve the people sincerely, and behave
themselves and welcome supervision.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he emphasizes the crucial role of the major figure of
any party or government unit, saying that the leader is equal to
other leading members and, meanwhile, he plays a especially
important part.  
</P>
</TEXT>
