<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Ex-freedom Fighters Get Grinding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean National Liberation
War Veterans Association (ZNLWVA) Wednesday distributed 1,000
grinding mills and 400 tractors to its members all over the
country.
</P>
<P>
The grinding mills and tractors were imported from China by
Sankorp Holdings, a company owned by the association.
</P>
<P>
Each province received 100 grinding mills and 40 tractors.
</P>
<P>
Chenjerai Hunzvi, chairman of the association told the
Zimbabwe News Agency that the tractors and the grinding mills
would go a long way in making the ex-freedom fighters
self-reliant in addition to creating employment for other people.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some members of the association finished a two-day
skills-training course to operate and repair the grinding mills
and the tractors.
</P>
<P>
The skill-training course was provided by Chinese technicians.
</P>
</TEXT>
