<HEADLINE> Exhibition On Tourist Items Opened in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 1 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on handicraft
articles and souvenirs for tourists opened today in Hangzhou,
capital of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The four-day showcase event attracted nearly 1,000 participants
from 120 enterprises in the province involved in the production of
items for tourists.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 varieties of items are on display.
</P>
<P>
The activity aims to give a boost to the development of local
products for tourists, which is expected to become a rising force
for local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 44 above-province-level producers of items
for tourists. And the products account for about 21 percent of the
local business turnover from tourism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
