<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Parliament Urges Yeltsin to Convene "Roundtable" Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Russia's parliament on Wednesday
called on President Boris Yeltsin to convene "roundtable" talks
on the formation of the new government.
</P>
<P>
The roundtable meeting is to be attended by four sides --
parliament deputies, the Presidential Administration, the
government and major political forces in the country.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin proposed the composition of the government without any
serious discussion with Russia's leading political forces, and his
demand for immediate approval of his nominations by the Duma does
not fit into constructive cooperation of federal authorities, said
Duma, lower house of the parliament, in a resolution passed with
273-40 vote.
</P>
<P>
However, the meeting of the four sides scheduled for Thursday
can be no substitute for the roundtable talks, said State Duma
Speaker Gennady Seleznyov, adding that the Duma is expected to
debate on Kiriyenko's nomination on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Federal Council, upper house of the parliament,
adopted the resolution by 138-3 with one abstention, saying the
roundtable meeting is needed for consultations on the composition
and policy of the new Cabinet and for working out a program to
overcome crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
The Council said its representatives should also attend the
State Duma's meeting on the formation of the new government.
</P>
</TEXT>
