<HEADLINE> S. Africa Should Explore SADC Market: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURB, April 1 (Xinhua) -- South African businesses
should make haste in accessing markets in the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) countries before they lost to
overseas competitors, Deputy Agriculture Minister Thoko Didiza
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 1998 World Canned Deciduous Fruit Conference in
Somerset West outside Cape Town, Didiza said that while the
region represented a market of about 130 million people, its
potential for local firms could be reduced if they had to compete
with multinational investors.
</P>
<P>
