<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Airlines Opens Lusaka-Washington Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Airlines will
begin direct flight to Lusaka, Zambia, as of April 2, 1998,
bringing its destinations to 26 in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here Wednesday, Bisrat Nigatu,
General Manager of the Ethiopian Airlines, Africa's biggest
airlines, said that the new flight will offer service twice a
week, every Thursday and Saturday from Addis Ababa to Lusaka and
the return flights will be every Friday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bisrat also announced that the airlines will begin direct
flight to Washington DC, the U.S. on June 4, bringing the number
of the airlines' destinations to 44 worldwide.
</P>
<P>
He said, travelers from the U.S. to east Africa had been
forced to transit through Europe and the direct flight service to
the U.S.Thursdays and Saturdays from Addis Ababa will ameliorate
the inconveniences of passengers.
</P>
<P>
He said the Ethiopian Airlines is operating actively to meet
the demands of its customers and maintain its international
standard.
</P>
<P>
The airlines brought into the country five Fokker planes
recently in addition to launching several local and foreign
routes, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
