<HEADLINE> Papandreou: Balkan's Future Depends on Balkan Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Greek Alternate Foreign Minister
George Papandreou said Wednesday that the Balkan countries must
take the future of the region in their hands and influence the
shaping of Europe as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a two-day conference here on the European Union-led
"Process for Stability and Good Neighborliness in Southeast
Europe," Papandreou stressed that the Balkan people should be able
to deal with problems and crises of the region.
</P>
<P>
He said that resolving the Kosovo problem would be a major test
for the potential of Balkan countries to cooperate peacefully and
constructively.
</P>
<P>
Papandreou believed that the parties concerned would resolve
the Kosovo problem through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
He hailed the start of European Union's expansion as "a
historic step," saying that the Balkan countries shared the common
prospect of integration into Europe.
</P>
<P>
The European integration could not be completed without the
Balkan countries' participation, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
