<HEADLINE> Jordan Welcomes Israeli Decision on South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Jordan on Wednesday welcomed an
Israeli decision to accept a U.N. resolution calling for its
withdrawal from south Lebanon, but underlined that Israel should
implement it "unconditionally."
</P>
<P>
"The official statement of the Israeli government announced
today sets an organized stand regarding Israel's preparedness to
accept resolution 425 and withdraw from Lebanon," said Deputy
Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Jawad Anani, quoted by
Jordan's official news agency.
</P>
<P>
"Israel's preparedness to withdraw from south Lebanon is a
more advanced stand than its previous ones, nevertheless it
contains conditions that are not available in the Security
Council's resolution 425," Anani said.
</P>
<P>
Israel's adoption of such a step in this direction was the
right thing, he added.
</P>
<P>
Israel's inner cabinet on Wednesday morning approved, with
conditions attached, the 20-year-old U.N. resolution calling for
immediate and unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
It insisted that implementation of the resolution should follow
negotiated security arrangements with Lebanese government in the
area it wanted to quit, a pre-condition strongly rejected by
Beirut.
</P>
<P>
Anani also urged Israel to respond positively to a proposal
raised by the United States on Israel's second troop redeployment
in the West Bank, and to implement with good faith the Hebron
accord which it signed with the Palestinians in January last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
