<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Port Urges for Better Role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's Tanga port
authorities called on the Tanzanian government to make full use
of the port to improve the port's sluggish business.
</P>
<P>
The Port Manager, Idi Mkwata, has complained that tea which is
at present being auctioned in Mombasa, Kenya, is transported by
road instead of using the port facility, reports reaching here
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mkwata told the Tanga Regional Commissioner Captain George
Mkuchika who inspected the port recently that the government
should establish a tea auction center in the country and use the
port as a route for export consignments.
</P>
<P>
The port official also urged the government to build a railway
from the northern town of Arusha to Musoma on the shore of the
Lake Victoria, to serve cargo to and from neighboring countries
such as Uganda, Rwanda and Burundi.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the manager suggested that the government
review the proposal of building an oil pipeline from Dar es
Salaam to Rwanda.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on capital investment plans from the year 1996 to
2001, Mkwata said the port will launch an economic processing
zone (EPZ). Terms of reference have been worked out and the port
are seeking technicians to study the issue, he added.
</P>
<P>
"By the end of December this year the study will be ready," he
said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Mkwata said the port authorities are making
efforts to win the ownership of the Mwambani bay for future
development. Since late 1980s, the bay has been under a 20-year
plan as the future port because it has deep berths for ship
anchoring, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The port has already paid some 84 million shillings (about
126,000 U.S. Dollars) as compensations for the resettlement of
Ndumi villagers living in the area, he said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Tanga Port, a major port along the Indian
Ocean, handled 108,500 tons of cargo but suffered a loss of 1.5
billion shillings, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
