<HEADLINE> France Increasing Investment In Shanghai's Urban Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The French government plans to
grant about 350 million US dollars (or two billion French francs)
worth of loans for subway construction in Shanghai, according to a
French official.
</P>
<P>
French companies will fund a garbage disposal plant in the
Pudong New Area and will bid for a number of large municipal
projects for streetcars, liquefied natural gas, and high-speed
railways.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai now has more than 90 French-funded projects, involving
nearly 170 million US dollars worth of investment, and there are
more than 50 small and medium-sized French companies doing
business in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The investment of French companies in Shanghai rose 30 percent
last year over the 1996 figure. France will increase investment in
hi-tech areas in China, especially in the fields of airplane
manufacturing, telecoms, and environmental protection.  
</P>
