<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan Visits Memorial to Zhou Enlai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, a member of the
Standing Committee of the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau,
paid a visit to the Memorial Hall of Premier Zhou Enlai and his
wife Deng Yingchao today in the north China Municipality of
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
Li, also chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, laid a wrath in front
of their statues and visited the exhibits on the lives of the
revolutionary couple.
</P>
<P>
Li, who was accompanyed by Tianjin mayor and Communist Party
chief, Zhang Lichang, said the beloved couple's great achievements
and immortal merits should be remembered from generation to
generations and that people should work for what they worked for,
dedicating their lives to the emancipation of the Chinese people,
the founding of New China, the country's socialist modernization
drive, and the great cause of Communism.
</P>
<P>
The hall opened on February 28. Tianjin is where the couple had
spent their college years.
</P>
<P>
Zhou was China's premier until he passed away on January 8,
1976. Deng was one of the few women proletarian revolutionaries to
take part in the famous Long March of 1934 to 1936 of the CPC-led
Red Army. She was also a former chairperson of the CPPCC National
Committee. 
</P>
