<HEADLINE> Trading On The Shanghai Stock Exchange Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The composite index on the
Shanghai Stock finished today at 1,269.01 today, up 14.05 points
from the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The exchange had a turnover of more than 10 billion yuan, a
record for the past few weeks.
</P>
<P>
This feat came just a day after the exchange implemented a new
rule requiring all investors who have trading accounts at the
Shanghai Stock Exchange to do their transactions through
designated securities operations.
</P>
<P>
According to the rules, investors have to name a securities
operation as trustee for stock trading and clearing services.
</P>
<P>
The new practice is intended to help improve practices and
market supervision, control risks, and curb securities-related
crimes. 
</P>
