<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Reserves Rise in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africa Reserve Bank's
provisional gross gold and foreign exchange reserves climbed
steadily to 32.8 billion Rand (6.53 billion U.S. Dollars) at the
end of March, the central bank said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This was 1.9 billion Rand (378 million Dollars) more than the
30.9 billion Rand (6.16 billion Dollars) attained in February
this year, South African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The utilization of foreign credit lines at the end of March
amounted to 9.2 million Rand (1.83 million Dollars), slightly up
from the 9.1 billion Rand (1.81 million Dollars) in February.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said its net oversold foreign exchange open
position was down at 12.8 billion Dollars from 14 billion Dollars
in February.  
</P>
