privatization of three major public sector banks, expected to be
sold off in 1998.
</P>
<P>
As part of its program to restructure the banking sector, the
government announced that it would pursue the default cases but
recent indications were that it had failed in its attempts.
</P>
<P>
However, analysts believed that Thursday's announcement that
cases against 3,400 loan defaulters had been finalized raised
hopes that the government was serious in recovering the loans.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that the market reacted positively to the
government's announcement over pursuing bank defaulters but if
there is no action forthcoming, there could be a reversal in the
stock market in the coming days. 
