<HEADLINE> Lucent Technologies' Chinese SDH Training Center Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Global telecommunications leader
Lucent Technologies opened a transmission technology training
center at Beijing's University of Posts and Telecommunications
today.
</P>
<P>
The "China Telecom/BUPT SDH Laboratory", the first laboratory
for synchronous digital hierarchy (SDH) technology in China, will
be used by telecommunications engineers and university students
and teachers to increase their SDH knowledge.
</P>
<P>
The lab is equipped with some of Lucent's most advanced SDH
systems, high-capacity optical multiplexing equipment, a flexible
digital interconnection system, and intelligent network management
software.
</P>
<P>
SDH technology, which was first developed by Bell Laboratories,
the R&AMP;D arm of Lucent, in the late 1980s, has become one of the
most extensively-used transmission systems in optical
telecommunications today. Lucent introduced the technology to
China in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The company has SDH optical cables trunks in Beijing, Shanghai,
Guangzhou, Shenzhen and other Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
According to Randy Yeh, chairman of Lucent Technologies
(China) Ltd., Lucent has developed two joint laboratories in
Shanghai Jiaotong University and Beijing University in the past
few months as part of its long-term development strategy in
China. The SDH training system at the University of Posts and
Telecommunications signals a big step forward in the company's
efforts to increase cooperation with China's universities and
telecoms industry here, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
