<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Spokesman Addresses Asia-Europe Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China attaches great importance to
positively supporting the process of Asia-European cooperation,
according to comments made by Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu
Bangzao during today's regular press conference.
</P>
<P>
When asked about China's view of Asia-European cooperation
prior to the forthcoming Asia-Europe Meeting, Zhu said that
strengthening cooperation and dialog between Asia and Europe is an
important reflection of increasing multipolarization.
</P>
<P>
Asia and Europe have witnessed the increasing momentum of
cooperation since the first Asia-Europe Meeting was held in
Bangkok in 1996, said Zhu, adding that follow-up activities have
proceeded smoothly and yielded fruitful results.
</P>
<P>
China attaches great importance to the forthcoming Second
Asia-Europe Meeting in London, and sincerely hopes the meeting
will further advance cooperation between Asian and European
nations in the realm of economic, trade and technological
exchanges. Zhu also pointed out that China fully agrees that Asia
and Europe should initiate dialog related to international finance
and related currencies.
</P>
<P>
China is fully prepared to join with all participants to ensure
the success of the meeting, and contribute to expanding
Asia-European ties, said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji, who will attend the meeting, will
also hold a summit with British Prime Minister Tony Blair, the
current EU president, and European Commission President Santer
prior to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
They will exchange views on Sino-EU bilateral ties and
wide-ranging issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Zhu described the summit as a major event in the history of
China-EU relations, and expressed his firm belief that it will
have a positive and far-reaching impact on efforts to further
promote the development of relations between the two sides.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
