<HEADLINE> Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Annan Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China attaches great importance to
the role the United Nations plays in world affairs and has
consistently supported the efforts of Secretary-General Kofi
Annan, according to Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao.
</P>
<P>
Zhu responded to a question at today's regularly scheduled
press conference by noting that the Chinese government also
attaches great importance to Annan's visit to China.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that Annan and Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen held
highly beneficial and constructive talks and exchanged in-depth
views on the current international situation, as well as the role
of the UN and weapons inspections in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin met Annan earlier today,
according to Zhu.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations currently faces severe challenges in
safeguarding world peace and stability, and in effectively
resolving political, economic and social problems, said Zhu,
adding that Annan shoulders important missions in related areas.
</P>
<P>
Annan has won high praise from the international community for
his extensive efforts to promote the constructive role of the UN,
as well as for his courage and outstanding diplomatic prowess in
handling the Iraqi weapons inspection crisis, said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
The UN, the world's most powerful and authoritative
inter-governmental organization, plays a unique role in
international affairs and cannot be replaced by any country or
any group of countries, said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Annan recently visited Baghdad and successfully mediated an
agreement to defuse the Iraqi weapons inspection crisis, a fact
which fully demonstrates that the UN can play a due role in
effectively promoting the resolution of major international
issues. Zhu stressed that China will continue to expand its
cooperation with the UN. 
</P>
</TEXT>
