<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman Comments on European Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu
Bangzao told a routine press conference here today that economic
and technological cooperation will be high on the agenda of the
second Asia-Europe Meeting scheduled for April 3-4 in London.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said Asia-Europe cooperation, economic coordination, and
financial crises and other international and regional issues of
common concern will be discussed, and the Chairman Statement, the
Asia-Europe Co-operation Framework, the ASEM Investment Promotion
Action Plan, and the ASEM Trade Facilitation Action Plan will all
be passed.
</P>
<P>
The Asia-Europe Vision Group and the Asia-Europe Environmental
Technology Center will be established and the Third Asia-Europe
Business Forum will be held, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The Asian financial crisis will also be a major topic, he said,
and China supports the ASEAN nations' suggestion that separate
statements be issued, and hopes that Asian and European countries
will increase coordination to help get countries out of trouble at
an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
China is not in opposition to a political dialogue with Europe
on the basis of equality and mutual benefits, he said, but such
dialogue should be conducted gradually in the spirit of seeking
common ground while preserving differences.
</P>
<P>
China believes that the Asia-Europe Meeting should be based on
a consensus reached through consultations, the spokesman said,
adding that the country welcome all follow-up actions that are in
conformity with the interests of all member countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
