<HEADLINE> Deutsche Bank Profit Drops Due to Asian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest commercial bank
Deutsche Bank Thursday said in Frankfurt that its pre-tax profit
was two billion marks (1.08 billion U.S. dollars) in 1997, down
from 4.9 billion marks (2.6 billion dollars) the year before.
</P>
<P>
It blamed the decline on extra risk provisions for its business
in Asia as a result of the financial crisis there, and on the
costs of restructuring as well.
</P>
<P>
The bank expects that the restructuring, which will cost 2.5
billion marks (1.4 billion dollars) in the next three years, will
help raise its annual earnings to some nine billion marks (4.9
billion dollars) by the year 2001. 
</P>
</TEXT>
