<HEADLINE> Chinese Legislator Meets Russian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of
the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee,
expressed the hope today for strengthed exchanges and cooperation
between judiciaries in China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang met with Yakovlev Veniamin, chairman of Russia's Supreme
Arbitration Court, and noted that the latter's visit will promote
bilateral exchanges and cooperation between courts and judicial
departments, especially cooperation in the realm of arbitration.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, a former vice-premier, held first official meeting with
a foreign official in his present capacity. He briefed Veniamin on
China's political and economic situation, as well as legislative
work, and noted that the nation has recorded monumental progress
over the past two decades in efforts to refine its legal system.
</P>
<P>
A socialist legal framework with Chinese characteristics based
on the nation's Constitution has primarily been established and
has played an important role in the country's reform and
modernization drive, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also addressed the establishment and growth of the
socialist market economy and noted the increasing importance of
legislative, judicial and arbitration efforts.
</P>
<P>
China is currently strengthening legislative and judicial work,
said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Veniamin said discussions and exchanges concerning legislative
and judicial activities have enabled him to gain a greater
understanding of China's judiciary and that increased exchanges
will further promote professional cooperation between the two
nations.
</P>
<P>
He expressed great appreciation for the progress recorded by
China's economic and judicial sectors.
</P>
<P>
Veniamin is visiting China at the invitation of the Chinese
Supreme People's Court. Court president Xiao Yang attended today's
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
