<DOCNO> XIE19980402.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK to Realize Sustained Development: Tung Chee Hwa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong government is
determined to realize the concept of "sustainable development"
which aims to ensure the continued competitiveness of Hong Kong in
the long run and a better living environment for generations to
come.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, made these remarks at the opening ceremony
of a five-day exhibition on the subject here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said: "In formulating policies, the Administration will
adhere to the principle of 'sustainable development' and take it
as a blueprint as we march into the 21st century."
</P>
<P>
In accordance with this principle, Tung said, far-sighted and
appropriate planning would enable the government to launch
large-scale development projects while taking due care of the
environment as well as protecting public interests at different
levels.
</P>
<P>
"In the course of development, we should take all our economic,
social and environmental objectives into account," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tung mentioned some problems such as air quality, marine and
river pollution that can not be overlooked, saying that the
government had launched a study on "sustainable development" in
Hong Kong for the 21st century in order to establish a tailor-made
strategic mechanism to assess the long-term impact of each
development project.
</P>
<P>
"The success of 'sustainable development' depends on the
support and participation by the general public," he said, adding
that the government would in due course consult various
organizations on the implementation of this concept", he said.
</P>
<P>
Through this exhibition, Tung said: "We wish to explain to the
Hong Kong people how 'sustainable development' is closely linked
with our everyday life and hope that this concept can take root in
our community." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
