<HEADLINE> German Ford Achieves Profits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Ford-Werke AG, the German subsidiary
of the Ford car company, said Thursday in Cologne that it achieved
42.6 million marks (23.5 million U.S. dollars) in profit last
year, compared with a loss of 551.4 million marks (304.2 dollars)
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The company reported a turnover of 28.1 billion marks (15.5 billion
dollars), up 6.4 percent, with sales up 1.4 percent to 1.14 million
cars, thanks to a 4.7 percent rise in exports.
</P>
<P>
Ford noted a four percent drop in sales at home. The company's
output last year rose 1.7 percent to 993,000 cars. 
</P>
