<HEADLINE> Philippine Police Hunting Killer Stalking Ramos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The police in the southern
Philippines are intensifying their manhunt operations against
fugitive Eduardo Iran who was allegedly hired to assassinate
President Fidel Ramos.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency Thursday quoted regional police
director Ricardo de Leon as saying that he received intelligence
reports that Iran was in Iloilo province, the southern part of the
country.
</P>
<P>
He added that prior to the alleged assassination reports from
the Presidential Palace, the regional police have made various
plans and employed different strategies to arrest Iran but failed.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Iran has been seen stalking Ramos in
recent months in a suspected assassination plot.
</P>
<P>
At a weekly press conference held Wednesday in the Presidential
Palace, Ramos confirmed the assassination plot, but said that he
would continue his style of coming near the people and leave the
plot for the police to investigate.
</P>
<P>
Iran, 47, was reportedly a discharged policemen. He is the
country's second wanted criminal carrying a reward of one million
pesos (about 26,315 U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
