<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Portugal Sign Science Cooperation Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China and Portugal signed a joint
statement here on Wednesday to enhance cooperation in science and
technology field.
</P>
<P>
A Eureka-Asia technological cooperation international meeting
is to be held every two years in Macao, according to the joint
statement signed by Chinese Minister of Science and Technology Zhu
Lilan and her Portuguese counterpart Mariano Gago.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be joined by research centers and companies
from China, Europe and other Asian countries, and aims at looking
for joint development of new technologies and products.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will also hold regular meetings to continue
scientific and technological exchanges, particularly on advanced
technologies and their industrial applications, the statement
says.
</P>
<P>
It stresses that both parties will take note and support the
forthcoming organization of an International Forum on Scientific
and Technological Culture in Europe and Asia to held in Macao in
the middle of next year.
</P>
<P>
A working group of Chinese and Portuguese experts will be
appointed to do prospective studies of the strategic potential
and the current situation of the science and advanced training
systems in Macao, according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement was based on a memorandum of understanding signed
in Beijing when Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio visited China
last year. Previously, China and Portugal signed an agreement on
scientific and technological cooperation in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Lilan said that cooperation between the two countries has
proceeded very smoothly since 1993, and the new statement will
further push forward cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Mariano Gago said that scientific and technological
cooperation between the two countries will help promote such
cooperation between Europe and Asia.
</P>
<P>
Currently, an "Eureka Meets Asia" event, including a
technological exhibition, is being held in Macao. It is the first
time Eureka stepped out of Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
