<HEADLINE> Nigerian Players to Go to France '98 With Wives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Members of Nigeria's national team
Super Eagles will go to France '98 World Cup with their wives if
they wish, coach Bora Milutinovic said Wednesday in Abuja.
</P>
<P>
"When players are with their wives and spouse, it would not
only reduce tension and anxiety but, save them from the hands of
other girls who could divert their attentions," the Serbian coach
said in a chat with reporters.
</P>
<P>
The players, however, will stay with their wives and will be
barred from going to night clubs during the matches, the coach
said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Milutinovic also warned over the overrating of the
Super Eagles both in and outside Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
"It is good to be optimistic, but it is also good to take it
easy or we may be dragged behind when we (are) over confident," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Milutinovic returned to Nigeria last Sunday. Since taking over
the job in early January, he had spent most of his time in Europe
to assess Nigerian players playing in various clubs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
