<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Jolts Padang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- An tectonic Earthquake measuring
6.4 on the Richter scale jolted the cities of Padang and Pariaman
in Indonesia's West Sumatra province in the small hours of
Thursday, reports reaching here from Padang said.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at early morning and lasted for 15
seconds, was so strong that it made a number of residents in the
two cities run out of their houses, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Head of the provincial Meteorology and Geophysical Agency Heru
Norman said the epicenter of the quake was at 2.12 degrees
southern latitude and 98.6 degrees eastern longitude 36 kilometers
deep in the sea, or about 180 kilometers southwest of Pariaman.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report of casualties but 15 houses were
cracked during the tremor, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Heru said there were also three aftershocks following the first
quake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
