<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombo Port Alerted to Tighten Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Colombo port has been ordered to
tighten its security after information was received that Tamil
rebels have planned to bring in explosives in a reefer container
and to enter the Colombo harbor, Security sources here said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said ships entering the harbor will be subjected to
full screening before being allowed into the inner harbor and the
authorities has also been alerted to be vigilant on the ownership
of such containers.
</P>
<P>
At present the Sri Lankan Navy is in charge of security in the
port, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The port of Colombo, one of the best in South Asia, is gearing
itself to become a hub in the region in competition with highly
developed ports such as Singapore and Hong Kong, port authorities
said.
</P>
<P>
The Colombo port is now a target of attack by the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam which has been fighting for a separate state
in the north and east of the country since 1983.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels launched a massive assault on the port in
April, 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
