<HEADLINE> Hickman's Euro Record Ratified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 2 (Xinhua) -- European swimming's ruling body LEN
has ratified the European short-course men's 100 meters butterfly
record of 51.40 seconds set by Britain's James Hickman in Sydney
on January 22, according to reports here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The time, confirmed after the paperwork had been completed,
overrides the 51.46 swum by Hickman at the concluding World Cup
meeting in Paris last Sunday which had been called a European
record by the organizers, the reports said. 
