<HEADLINE> China Promotes Middle East Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua)-- China will join the international
community in continuing efforts to advance the Middle East peace
process, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government has always maintained that the
sovereignty and territorial integrity of Lebanon must be
respected, and the relevant United Nations resolutions on Middle
East issues be implemented entirely and unconditionally," said Zhu
during a press conference sponsored by the Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
"We are cognizant of the fact that Israel has declared it will
accept UN Security Council Resolution 425 on withdrawal from
southern Lebanon," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China appreciates and supports efforts of the UN
and various countries for advancing the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said deadlocks can be avoided and the peace process will
continue to progress as long as Middle East peace talks conform to
relevant UN resolutions and the principle of "land for peace," and
related parties adopt flexible and pragmatic stands with no
additional conditions attached. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
