<DOCNO> XIE19980402.0154 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets UN Chief (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
that China will continue to support the work of the United
Nations, as always, in a meeting with visiting United Nations
Secretary-General Kofi Annan here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the United Nation's role has drawn ever more
attention during the development of multiple centers of power in
the world, especially after the Cold War. The United Nations,
under reduced restrictions, has become more vigorous and raised
the expectations of all countries.
</P>
<P>
So, Jiang said, the United Nations should exert more effort to
play its due role, which is undoubtedly conducive to pushing the
development of the emergence of multiple influencing powers.
</P>
<P>
He continued that after taking office as the U.N.
secretary-general, Annan has made many attempts at reforming the
United Nations, and that China sincerely hopes the United Nations,
through reform and adjustment, can better adapt itself to the
demands of new situations, and handle international issues in a
more fair and effective way, so as to make further achievements in
safeguarding peace and promoting development.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that the U.N.'s success needs the support and
cooperation of all its member states, and spoke highly of Jiang's
and the Chinese government's support and contributions, adding
that China's participation in, and support of, the United Nations
is vital to its role in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his thanks for China's firm support for his handling
of the recent weapons inspection crisis in Iraq, Annan said that
in a crucial time China's position on a peaceful resolution and
support for diplomatic efforts played a vital role in solving the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Annan said he hoped that the cooperative relations between the
United Nations and China would continue and deepen.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Iraqi issue is another serious international
crisis after the Cold War, especially after the Gulf War,
Jiang praised Annan for his courage, wisdom and diplomatic skills
in his successful Iraqi trip for political coordination at a time
when war was imminent.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he has been concerned about the situation and has
exchanged letters with leaders of several countries expounding
China's position aiming for a peaceful resolution.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the memorandum of understanding reached between
the United Nations and the Iraqi government can be carried out in
a down-to-earth manner so that the issue of weapons inspection can
be fundamentally resolved.
</P>
</TEXT>
