<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third New Offshore Oil Field Found in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Angola National Petroleum
Corporation said in a news release that a third new offshore oil
field was found in No. 15 water area by Esso Exploration Angola
Limited.
</P>
<P>
The release available here Thursday said that this new oil
field was discovered in No. 15 waters 1,289 meters under sea
level, 360 kilometers northwest of the Capital city of Luanda.
</P>
<P>
Well Marimba found in the same waters has already begun
producing oil. According to tests, the well can produce 6,800
barrels of oil per day.
</P>
<P>
The release said that Esso will carry out the full exploration
to determine the exact reserve of this newly-found offshore oil
field.
</P>
<P>
Esso Exploration Angola Limited is a subsidiary of Exxon
Corporation. And this is the second time that the company has
discovered an oil field in the Angolan waters.
</P>
<P>
So far, three deep sea oil fields have been discovered this
year in Angola.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Esso discovered on March 12 Well
Kissanje-1 in the same water area, which is now in trial
production and its output per day has reached 10,000 barrels.
</P>
<P>
On March 11, the Angola National Petroleum issued a news
release, declaring that Elf Exploration Angola, a subsidiary of
the French Elf Exploration, discovered an oil field with large
reserves and high-quality oil in Rosa-1 Well 1,405 meters under
sea level, some 200 kilometers northwest of Luanda.
</P>
<P>
In trial production period, the well now produces 12,000
barrels of oil per day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
