<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets UN Chief (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang, calling Annan an old friend, said this is the fourth
time they have met within a year, and Annan has chosen a good time
to visit since new state and government leaders have been selected
in China. He said he hopes Annan can take advantage of this
opportunity to make some new friends, which will help further the
friendship and cooperation between China and the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed out that the United Nations has advantages in
dealing with international affairs and its role is irreplaceable.
</P>
<P>
Annan said he is pleased to be able to exchange views with
Jiang on international issues and U.N. affairs, offering his
congratulations on China's achievements in economic reforms and
its important role in dealing with the financial crisis in
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
He said he will cooperate with the new Chinese government,
adding that he is expecting to meet with new Chinese Premier Zhu
Rongji.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that, after the Cold War, international situations
have undergone great change, the trend toward the existence of
multiple influencing powers has increased, relations between big
powers are under strategic adjustment, various partnerships are
gradually evolving into mechanisms, and the concept of
independence, seeking self-development through association and a
coordinated development has grown among all countries.
</P>
<P>
Developing countries have increased their overall strength and
becoming an important force in the international arena, said
Jiang, adding that the economic element is playing an increasing
role in international relations and the interdependent relations
among countries have become stronger.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said his meetings with leaders of some countries not long
ago have led to a wide-ranging consensus on international and
bilateral affairs.
</P>
<P>
The relations among big powers in the world tend to be stable,
which is not only in the interests of the concerned countries but
also significant in promoting peace and prosperity in the world in
the 21st century, Jiang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
