<HEADLINE> Kenya to Host Regional Military Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Kenya will host a regional peace
support operation scheduled to be held in June in northwestern
Kenya, the Kenya Times reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The daily newspaper said that the code named "Exercise Natural
Fire 1998" military exercise would take three weeks from June 3
to June 27 and more than 2,000 combat troops from the United
States, Tanzania, Uganda and Kenya are due to participate.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted a statement issued by Kenyan Defense
Department as saying that troops from U.S. Central Command and
the European Command would take part in the exercise.
</P>
<P>
"American troops from the two commands will conduct initial
training on peace support operations in both Uganda and Tanzania
prior to their concentration in Kenya for the exercise," the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
The combat troops which include the infantry, gunners, tanks,
paratroopers and air force personnel from the four countries will
participate in the peace keeping military exercise, it added.
</P>
