<HEADLINE> New Romanian Premier Confirmed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu Thursday appointed 55 year-old economist Radu
Vasile as premier following his predecessor quit the government
three days ago.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said Vasile, who takes over from Victor Ciorbea who
resigned Monday, "has the important task of giving Romania a stable and
effective government."
</P>
<P>
Under the Romanian constitution, the new premier will have 10
days to form a new cabinet. He will have the twin tasks of
overcoming long-standing coalition turmoil and getting the
country's economy back on track.
</P>
<P>
Vasile acted as the vice-chairman of the Senate from 1992 to
1996 and was re-elected to the post in the 1996 parliamentary
elections. 
