<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Leader Meets With Namibian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a Standing Committee
member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), met with a delegation from South
West Africa People's Organization (SWPO) of Namibia led by its
General Secretary H. Pohamba.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also Chinese vice-president, said that the Chinese and
Namibian peoples have shared a profound traditional friendship
though the two countries are geographically far from each
other. CPC and the Chinese government have consistently supported
Namibian people's just struggle for national independence and
against racial segregation, said Hu.
</P>
<P>
China is pleased with the achievements scored by Namibia under
the leadership of President Sam Nujoma since the country became
independent.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Sino-Namibian ties have witnessed new progress
in recent years, with frequent exchange of high-level visits and
the expansion of bilateral cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Hu expressed the belief that the current China visit by the
delegation would further advance the friendly and cooperative ties
between the two parties and the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Hu also briefed the Namibian visitors on China's reform and
opening up.
</P>
<P>
Pohamba conveyed to Hu a letter from President Nujoma to
Chinese President Jiang Zemin, who is also the general-secretary
of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that the SWPO and CPC started friendly exchanges more
than 30 years ago and the SWPO hopes to expand the existing
cooperative relations with the CPC through the delegation's current
China tour.
</P>
<P>
Pohamba expressed thanks to CPC and the Chinese government for
their consistent support to Namibia and said that China has won the
respect of the international community through its consistent
support to the just cause of developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Pohamba reiterated that his country will stick to the "one
China" policy and will not have any official relations with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Pohamba and his party are here as guests of CPC.  
</P>
