<HEADLINE> Some 800 South Koreans Infected With AIDS Virus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 776 South Koreans have
been founded carrying the AIDS virus, or HIV, by the end of March,
the Ministry of Health and Welfare said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Of the HIV carriers, about 70 percent are aged between 20-30
and 70 percent are men, the ministry said. In the first three
months of this year, 29 people were infected with the virus and 12
of them died.
</P>
<P>
A controversy over childbirth by mothers carrying HIV has
flared up again in South Korea after a HIV-positive female in her
30s gave birth to a boy at a Seoul hospital last month.
</P>
<P>
Since 1989, the country has registered 10 cases of childbirth
by women with the AIDS virus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
