<HEADLINE> South Africans Keen to Invest in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africans are keen to invest
in Zambia, a Zambia Investment Center (ZIC) statement has said.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia Thursday quoted a ZIC statement issued here
Wednesday as saying that some members of the Southern African
Chamber of Agriculture Development in Africa (SACADA) said they
are willing to come to Zambia and establish large-scale farms.
</P>
<P>
They expressed their willingness after a two-week investment
promotion mission in South Africa by Commerce, Trade and Industry
Minister Knoch Kavindele last month.
</P>
<P>
SACADA, which represents the interest of commercial farmers in
South Africa, is expected to send a delegation to Zambia on a
site inspection tour soon, according to the daily newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Other organizations which have shown interest in investment in
Zambia includes the Development Bank of South Africa and some
fund managers.
</P>
<P>
Bokomo Co. will also send a representative to Zambia soon to
follow up a number of issues raised during the mission.
</P>
<P>
Kavindele and his party also held meetings with over six
chambers of commerce and industry of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Currently, South Africa is the biggest investor in Zambia.
</P>
