Khalid Ikram, head of IMF's Egypt department, said on Wednesday
that Egypt's inflation rate was reduced to 5 percent in 1997,
compared with 20 percent in 1990, and the budget deficit was less
than 1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak met with his Palestinian
counterpart Yasser Arafat in Sharm El Sheikh on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
They probed the difficulties in the peace process between the
Palestinians and Israel, and ways and means of breaking the
deadlock.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa on Wednesday conferred
with United States Ambassador Daniel Kurtzer in Cairo about the
Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
Kurtzer said after the meeting that they exchanged views on the
outcome of U.S. peace envoy Dennis Ross' recent talks with Arafat
and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on ways of reviving
the peace talks. 
