<HEADLINE> Utah's Sloan Named NBA Coach of March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Jerry Sloan guided the Utah Jazz
to a 15-2 record during the month to win the NBA Coach of the
Month for Marth.
</P>
<P>
Jazz recorded a 10-2 on the road and clinched a playoff spot
for the 14th consecutive season, the second longest active streak
behind Portland (15) and the sixth longest streak in the NBA
history.
</P>
<P>
Sloan, with a win-loss record of 630 to 377 games, coached in
the 1,000th game of his career on March 16 at Minnesota and moved
ahead of Doug Moe (628) into 13th place on the all-time victories
list with a win at Dallas on March 27.
</P>
<P>
For the month, Utah ranked first in the NBA in points per game
(104.1), field goal percentage (.502) and free throw percentage
(.797), and fifth in three-point field-goal percentage (.411).
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for the Coach of the Month were Charlotte's
Dave Cowens, Chicago's Phil Jackson, Cleveland's Mike Fratello,
the Los Angeles Lakers' Del Harris, Miami's Pat Riley and
Orlando's Chuck Daly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
