<HEADLINE> Chinese Ad Agencies to Provide Integrated Marketing Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China's advertising agencies
should provide customers with intergrated marketing services, an
official of the State Administration of Industry and Commerce has
said.
</P>
<P>
The official, Zheng Heping, was quoted by the International
Business Daily as saying that Chinese ad agencies should set up an
intergrated marketing service system that includes media services,
creative communications, image-building, direct marketing and
public relations services.
</P>
<P>
This is to meet the needs of Chinese enterprises which are
seeking to compete in the global market, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ad agencies should learn from their foreign counterparts and
make use of modern technology to make progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
Awaking from the almost blank in the 1980s, China's advertising
business has rocketed to 46.2 billion yuan in 1997. There were
57,000 advertising businesses, of which more than 100 were joint
ventures with foreign companies. And 545,000 people were employed
in this field.
</P>
<P>
The cities of Shanghai, Beijing and the province of Guangdong
have emerged as three centers for China's advertising, which
accounted for 44.5 percent of the nation's advertising business
earnings. 
</P>
