<HEADLINE> China Establishes Physics Education Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China has established its first
physics education network at Hangzhou University in
this capital of east China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The Center of China Physics Education Network, funded by the
China Physics Association, will link Chinese universities and
colleges with institutions of higher education throughout the
world via the INTERNET, CHINANET, and China Education and Research
Network.
</P>
<P>
The new network will provide wide-ranging information related
to the discipline, including educational developments, teaching
courses, research projects, exhibitions and associations.
</P>
<P>
Professor Ye Gaoxiang, the center's director, said the network
will provide researchers, teachers and students access to
worldwide exchanges related to advanced educational information.
</P>
