<HEADLINE> Philippine Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Export Earnings for the first two
months of 1998 increased by 23.9 percent to 4.342 billion U.S.
dollars from 3.505 billion dollars a year earlier, data released
by the Philippine National Statistics Office showed on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Receipts from exports in February amounted to 2.227 billion
dollars or 22.9 percent higher than 1.812 billion dollars in
February last year, the data showed.
</P>
<P>
With semi-conductor devices increasing by 85.5 percent, revenue
from exports of electronics and components rose by 46.5 percent to
1.115 billion dollars in February from 760.67 million a year ago.
</P>
<P>
This top dollar earner also accounted for a 50 percent of
aggregate receipts, according to the data.
</P>
<P>
The United States remained as the top market with receipts
posting a 12.2 percent growth in February to 731.31 million
dollars from 651.94 million dollars in 1997. 
</P>
