<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Chief Satisfied with Israeli Withdrawal from Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Secretary
General Kofi Annan has been encouraged by the decision that the
government of Israel has finally taken steps to withdraw its
forces from Lebanon, a press statement of the Secretary General
issued here today said.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary General and the Prime Minister of Israel Benjamin
Netanyahu spoke on the telephone last night after the formal
decision by the government of Israel to pull its forces out of
Southern Lebanon, the press statement said.
</P>
<P>
Secretary General Annan left here today for London after
Chinese President Jiang Zemin met with him. He arrived here
Tuesday for an official visit. During his stay in Beijing, he had
talks with Chinese vice-Premier Qian Qichen.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary General had raised the issue of Israel's
compliance with the UN Security Council resolution 425 in his
meetings with the Prime Minister and the Minister of Defense of
Israel, as well as with other concerned parties, during his recent
visit to the region," the statement added.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary General is encouraged that a decision has
finally been taken by the government of Israel to withdraw from
Lebanon. The implementation of this withdrawal will require
discussions with all concerned in order to be fully effective,"
the statement noted, adding that the Secretary General urges all
parties to cooperate in this process.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary General expresses his satisfaction that the
Security Council resolution adopted more than 20 years ago is at
last on the verge of implementation," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
