<HEADLINE> New Policy to Encourage Laid-Off Workers to Become Self-Employed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Labor Bureau has
adopted a new policy to encourage laid-off workers from
State-owned enterprises in the city to become self-employed.
</P>
<P>
The new policy stipulates that this year's laid-off workers will
receive 10,000 yuan (1,200 U.S. dollars) in subsidies if they
choose to become self-employed.
</P>
<P>
The number of newly displaced workers in Beijing this year
could reach 157,000. If all these workers become self-employed,
the city's labor departments will offer 1.5 billion yuan (180
million U.S. dollars) to them.
</P>
<P>
Currently, most of the laid-off workers in Beijing seek new
jobs after technical training with the help of labor departments.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
