<HEADLINE> Modern Japanese Calligraphy Exhibits in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of modern Japanese
calligraphy opened here this morning at the Museum of the Chinese
Revolution.
</P>
<P>
A total of 250 pieces of works of ancient Chinese characters,
Japanese syllabic script, seal cutting and other forms of the
calligraphic art, which represents the highest level of modern
Japanese calligraphy, are displayed at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Chen Junsheng, vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference National Committee, and Koike Tadao,
president of the Mainchi Newspapers of Japan, cut the ribbon for
the opening of the exhibition, which is jointly sponsored by
All-China Youth Federation and the Mainchi Newspapers of Japan,
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will last until 16 this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
