<HEADLINE> Standard Chartered Bank Optimistic About Zhuhai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Standard Chartered Bank of London
believes the Zhuhai Special Economic Zone is a good place for
business, said Lance Browne, the bank's chief executive officer in
charge of China and Macao affairs.
</P>
<P>
Speaking during a ceremony to mark the 10th anniversary of the
bank's Zhuhai Branch, Browne said Zhuhai has standardized banking
regulation and that the market has great potential.
</P>
<P>
As the first foreign bank opened in Zhuhai, the branch during
the past 10 years has established good business ties with local
state-owned and overseas-funded enterprises, and has granted
several billion U.S. dollars in loans.
</P>
<P>
Though headquartered in London, Standarded Chartered generates
two-thirds of its profits from Asia. It has opened eight branches
and eight representative offices in China.
</P>
<P>
Browne said the bank has chosen Zhuhai as a focus for business
in 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
