<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vasile Nominated Candidate For Romania's Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Romania's first ruling party,
the National Peasants' Party, nominated its general secretary and
spokesman Radu Vasile on Wednesday as candidate for prime minister.
</P>
<P>
Vasile said after the nomination that the new government will
endeavor to revise the draft budget, work to tap resources and
establish foundations to enhance the development of small-and
medium-sized businesses and to encourage exports.
</P>
<P>
Whatever difficulties are ahead, he said, the future government
will do its utmost to carry out reforms.
</P>
<P>
President Emil Constantinescu is expected to confirm the
nomination on Thursday. Once approved by the president, Vasile
will form the cabinet within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Following former Prime Minister Victor Ciorbea's resignation on
Monday, Minister of Industry and Trade Mircea Ciumara, Chairman of
the State Property Foundation Sorin Dimitriu, and Vasile ran for
the vacancy.
</P>
<P>
Forty-two of the 72 members in the leading group of the
National Peasants' Party cast favorable votes for Vasile.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the party Ion Diaconescu said it was within
expectations for Vasile to be chosen as candidate for prime
minister. The result has also been approved by all other parties.
</P>
<P>
He said, however, the prime minister has only limited power
since the government's policies need approval of the parliament
before they go into force.
</P>
<P>
Vasile acted as the vice-chairman of the Senate from 1992 to
1996 and was re-elected to the post in the 1996 parliamentary
elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
