<HEADLINE> Moldova's Communists Win Parliamentary Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Party of Moldovan Communists
was the big winner in the recent parliamentary elections by
capturing 40 seats of the total 101, the Central Election
Commission of Moldova announced Tuesday in Kishinev, capital of
Moldova.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the commission Dumitru Nidelcu said three other
parties, including the Democratic Convention, the Democratic and
Prosperous Moldova Bloc and the Party of Democratic Forces,
received more than 4 percent of the votes respectively, the
minimum number required to win seats in parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Party of Moldovan Communists received 30.01 percent of the
votes, while the Democratic Convention followed with 19.42 percent
and won 26 seats.
</P>
<P>
The turnout was 69.12 percent, or 1,680,470 people from the
2,324,300 eligible voters. Some 57,480 ballots were invalidated.
</P>
<P>
The parliamentary elections were held on March 22. It was the
second election since the former Soviet Union republic gained
independence in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
