<HEADLINE> Russia Opposes Sanctions on Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Russia strongly opposes the
enforcement of sanctions on Yugoslavia as a way to settle the
Kosovo issue, a Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the United Nations Security Council's decision on
Tuesday to impose an arms embargo on Yugoslavia, the spokesman
said the international community should continue working for
positive change in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
He said mediation by the international community should
encourage and support dialogue in the region and stop the
retrogression of its political process.
</P>
<P>
Enforced sanctions, particularly economic sanctions, he said,
would have a negative impact on the Balkan region and other
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the U.N. Security Council resolution on an arms embargo
was revised to avoid the escalation of regional tension and
facilitate the settlement of conflict through political means
while ensuring the territory integrity of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The resolution condemned the activities pursued by the
separatists and terrorists in Kosovo, and said foreign support for
such activities must be banned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
