<HEADLINE> Belgrade Slams U.N. Arms Embargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav government has
denounced the United Nations arms embargo as groundless and
unacceptable.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said in a statement that the embargo posed
an "unprecedented and unwarranted meddling " in its internal
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Pressures and interference from abroad are baseless,
counterproductive and harmful, the statement said, adding that
the embargo can only "encourage those whose aims are unreal and
dangerous."
</P>
<P>
Considering the situation in Kosovo posed no threat to
international stability and security, the U.N. was not justified
by its charter to discuss the issue, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Security Council imposed an arms embargo Tuesday to
pressure Belgrade to open unconditional dialogue with ethnic
Albanian leaders in the troubled Serbian province Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
