<HEADLINE> Canada to Buy British Submarines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian government has decided
to purchase four British submarines, reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The government is expected to announce Thursday that it is buying
the four used diesel subs to replace Canada's three aging Oberon-class
ones.
</P>
<P>
The British Upholder-class subs were built in the early 1990s
and mothballed soon after their delivery since the British navy
decided on nuclear-powered ships.
</P>
<P>
The Upholders cost about 350 million U.S. dollars each to
build. The exact price and financing has not yet been made public.
</P>
<P>
Canada's current subs were built by the British in the
1960s. For years, Canada's navy has been petitioning for new subs
to replace the old ones.
</P>
<P>
With the purchase, Canada's navy will have subs that are
reportedly more quiet, faster, dive deeper and require smaller
crews than the Oberons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
