<HEADLINE> Poles Protest Against EU Entry Negotiations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Poles in Warsaw, Krakow and other
cities have staged demonstrations against the country's entry into
the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
The protesters, mostly from the organizations such as "All
Poland Youth," the Party of Real Politics and the Polish National
Party, took to the streets as the government started formal
negotiations with the EU in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
Waving banners, they shouted, "No Entry into EU," "No
Maastricht, Just Poland," "To Hell with the EU" and "Poland for
the Polish."
</P>
<P>
Maruisz Dzierzawsky, chairman of the Party of Real Politics,
said that they opposed Poland's subordination to the EU.
</P>
<P>
He said the EU had been incapable of handling its own internal
affairs, was in stagnation, and all its commitments were frauds.
</P>
<P>
However, some Poles backed the government, organizing rallies
in support of an early entry.
</P>
<P>
Previous public opinion polls by newspapers showed that the
majority of Poles favored entry into the EU, with support at
higher than 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
All the major parties in Poland unanimously agree with the
entry application. However, support has declined recently to 65
percent in the opinion polls. 
</P>
