<HEADLINE> First Phase of Yellow River Theme Park Nears Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the first phase
of the Yellow River Grand View theme park in Zhengzhou, capital of
central China's Henan Province, is nearing completion. It is
scheduled to open for tourists in May.
</P>
<P>
The tourist project with Sino-Singapore financing, which will
be finished in three stages, was started in 1993. The total
planned investment for the Yellow River Grand View, covering an
area of 174 hectares, will be 80 million U.S. dollars, of which 18
million is being spent on the first phase.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, first-phase facilities include a
3.7-kilometer water course modeled after the Yellow River, a
30-meter tower, miniature scenes reflecting local customs and
folklore, an exhibition hall, a restaurant and a cinema.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River Grand View has been listed by the China
National Tourism Administration and Henan Province as one of the
decade-long tourism development projects running from 1991 to 2000
as well as a key project for a projected Yellow River national
tourism program.
</P>
<P>
The Zhengzhou-based Yellow River Tourism Development Corp. was
started by four Singapore companies and two Chinese firms in
1995. The Singapore companies have 65 percent of the
investment. The joint venture is taking charge of construction of
the Yellow River Grand View.
</P>
<P>
When all three construction phases are finished, the Yellow
River Grand View will be the largest theme park in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
