<HEADLINE> Province-Wide Social Security System Taking Shape in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A province-wide social security
system centering on unemployment and old-aged insurance has taken
shape in Central China's Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
An official from the provincial government said that since
1993, old-age insurance has covered nearly 15,000 state-owned
enterprises in the province, accounting for 46 percent of Hunan's
state-owned enterprises, benefiting 2.5 million workers.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government also expanded coverage of
unemployment insurance from state-owned enterprises to collective
enterprises and workers from the Chinese side in Sino-foreign
ventures.
</P>
<P>
About 22,000 enterprises with three million workers in Hunan
took part in the unemployment insurance.
</P>
<P>
Two other security systems such as medical and child-birth
insurance for female workers have started their trial operations;
and preparations have been completed on industrial injury
insurance.
</P>
<P>
The official pointed out that the emphasis should be given to
improving service levels of social security management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
