<HEADLINE> Brazil's Trade Deficit Reaches $670 Million in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Trade deficit in Brazil
reached 672 million U.S. dollars in March, the Ministry of
Industry, Commerce and Tourism said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The deficit resulted from a trade imbalance which saw 4.533
billion dollars of imports and 3.861 billion dollars of exports.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the country's trade deficit totalled about
1.4 billion dollars in the first three months of this year, a 42
percent reduction over the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
