<HEADLINE> Jordan Named Player of March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Michael Jordan of Chicago Bulls
was named on Wednesday the Player of the Month for his leading
role in helping the two-time defending champions to an NBA-best
13-1 record in March.
</P>
<P>
Jordan led the league in scoring by averaging 28.9 points, and
added 5.3 rebounds, 3.5 assists and 2.07 steals per game.
</P>
<P>
The four-time league MVP scored 20 or more points 12 times
during the month and at least 30 points on eight occasions.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, 35, currently leads the NBA in scoring at 28.3 points
per game in his attempt to top the league for a record 10th time
in his career.
</P>
<P>
Chicago owns the league's best record (56-17) with nine games
remaining in the regular season. 
</P>
