<HEADLINE> Seeded Hill Bows out of British Open Squash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The number eight seed Anthony Hill
of Australia was beaten 15-12, 9-15, 15-10, 15-6 by England's Paul
Johnson in the second round at the British Open squash
championship in Birmingham, England, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, the Hungarian Open champion, will next play defending
champion Jansher Khan of Pakistan in the quarter-final.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani rallied from 9-11 in the first game and 10-12
down in the second to beat the Australian Byron Davis 15-12,
15-13, 15-11.
</P>
<P>
Canadian world number three Jonathon Power's hopes of becoming
squash's world number one took a blow when his third ankle injury
within a few weeks forced him to quit the match against David
Evans of Wales 9-15, 15-17, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Power's misfortune gives Evans a quarter-final meeting with the
11th seed Dan Jenson of Australia, who had to save two match
points before winning 10-15, 10-15, 15-11, 15-14, 15-2 against
another Canadian Graham Ryding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
