<HEADLINE> Cuba, Spain Continue Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban government said the
appointment of a new Spanish ambassador to Cuba would normalize
diplomatic relations between the two countries, Cuban Foreign
Ministry spokesman Alejandro Gonzalez said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gonzalez made the remark after Spanish Prime Minister Jose
Maria Aznar announced that a new Spanish ambassador to Cuba would
be named Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Aznar gave no name, but official sources said it was likely to
be Eduardo Junco, who had been ambassador to the former Zaire and
Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
The post has been empty for the past 16 months since Cuban
authorities withdrew accreditation in December 1996 from the then
Spanish Ambassador Jose Coderch after he said he would open the
doors of the embassy to Cuban dissidents. Cuba has accused Spain
of interfering in its domestic affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
