<HEADLINE> Dalian Shipbuilder Launches Second Supertanker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Dalian Shipyard in northeast
China's Liaoning Province launched a second 110,000-dwt (dead
weight ton) supertanker for the Thenamaris Company of Greece late
last month.
</P>
<P>
The new plant is currently fabricating a third supertanker --
the "Seaqueen" -- for the Greek company.
</P>
<P>
Successful launches of the two supertankers symbolizes the
fact that China has gained a foothold in shipping market for
southern Europe. Greece is one of the world's major shipping
nations, with the nation's registered fleet accounting for 17
percent of the world's total deadweight tonnage.
</P>
<P>
The 110,000-dwt supertankers, which represent a new model
totally designed and developed by the Dalian Shipyard, feature
state-of-the-art design and offer total optimization
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The Dalian Shipyard has received orders for additional eight
110,000-dwt supertankers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
