<HEADLINE> Sampras Asks for Wild Card in Queen's Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 1 (Xinhua) -- After losing his top ranking spot
to Chile's Marcelo Rios, Pete Sampras has asked for a wild card
into the 750,000 U.S. dollars Queen's Club grass court tennis
championship, organisers said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tournament will take place on June 8-14, two weeks before
the Wimbledon Open, and one week after the French Open.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who has attained his No. 1 spot for 102 weeks, won the
Queen's title in 1995 but was beaten in the quarterfinals last
year by Sweden's Jonas Bjorkman.
</P>
<P>
Although eight of the world top 20 expressed their willingness
to compete in the 56-man draw, the tournament runs against another
grass court tournament at Halle, Germany, which offers more prize
money.
</P>
<P>
Four wild cards were still available and the organisers also
hoped to allure Andre Agassi to show up in the tournametnt, said
Ian Wight, director of the Queen's championship.
</P>
<P>
Among the big-name participants were U.S. Open titlist Pat
Rafter of Australia, Swedes Bjorkman and Thomas Enqvist and home
star Greg Rusedski. 
</P>
</TEXT>
