<HEADLINE> Increasing Machinery, Electronics Exports in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has 142 machinery and electronics manufacturers with
export licenses, which did 558 million US dollars worth of
business last year, almost four times the 1996 figure.
</P>
<P>
These companies account for 23 percent of local exports of
machinery and electronics products, a big increase from the former
7 percent, and 41 of them have more than a million US dollars
worth of exports each a year.
</P>
<P>
