<HEADLINE> Mexico to Host 1999 FIFA Confederations Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Mexico will take over Saudi
Arabia to host the FIFA Confederations Cup in 1999, the CONCACAF
announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After the first three Cups were played in Riyadh, Mexico has
come over to host the tournament of regional champions during the
first two weeks of January.
</P>
<P>
In the first editions, Argentina won the inaugural tournament
in 1992 with Denmark becoming titlest in 1995 and Brazil in 1997.
</P>
<P>
As Mexico playing host and defending CONCACAF champion, the
United States will qualify as runner-up from the North, Central
American and Caribbean region.
</P>
<P>
The other teams scheduled to compete in the FIFA Confederations
Cup are Asian champion Saudi Arabia, African champion Egypt, South
American runner-up Bolivia and defending champion Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The Oceania champion was still to be determined together with a
European squad to be announced later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
