<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Progress Achieved in Fenhe River Pollution Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The water quality of the upper
reaches of the Fenhe River has reached Grade-3 groundwater
standards thanks to strengthened pollution treatment efforts
carried out by north China's Shanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
In the past, numerous enterprises and mines located along the
Fenhe River in Shanxi, China's major energy and chemical industry
base, created serious pollution problems along the river.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has outlined detailed programs to
tackle related problems and protect the well-being of tens of
thousands of people living in the river valley.
</P>
<P>
Some 191 of the total 670 polluting enterprises along the river
have completed pollution treatment projects, with an additional
100 projects proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has punished 19 enterprises which
failed to meet treatment deadlines.
</P>
<P>
Arduous efforts carried out by governments at all levels have
led to significant improvements in water quality in both the
middle and low reaches of the river. 
</P>
