<HEADLINE> Asprilla Sidelined with Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Faustino Asprilla was plunged into
the sea of sadness when club doctors on Wednesday warned him
against play for a month to heal the leg injury.
</P>
<P>
Officials failed to minute the extent of the injury, but the
Colombian striker has to take the time to nurse his severe thigh
strain since his transfer from Newcastle to Parma in January.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Asprilla suffered another minor knee injury to cast
clouds over his prospect for Colombia in the World Cup finals to
be kicked off on June 10.
</P>
<P>
A Parma official said that medical examinations indicated that
Asprilla's condition worsened after his tour with the Colombian
national team. Earlier, Parma opposed Asprilla's departure for the
tour.
</P>
<P>
Upon his back to the club, the Colombia striker was checked by
team doctors on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"He will be sidelined for 40 days and will need more time to
get trained and regain form. His season with Parma is over," the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Asprilla, who has been troubled by injury time and again,
rejoined Parma on a 10 million U.S. dollars transfer fee.
</P>
<P>
Before moving to Newcastle in February 1996, he had played four
seasons with Parma scoring 25 goals in 84 league appearances.
</P>
</TEXT>
