<HEADLINE> Qinghai Province to Accelerate Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Qinghai provincial government will
collect funds to accelerate resource exploitation and
infrastructure construction, said Su Sen, deputy governor of the
northwest China's province.
</P>
<P>
As an inland province, Qinghai's economy is less developed. But
it has abundant resources such as minerals, hydro-power and
husbandry.
</P>
<P>
Su disclosed that adding input in fixed assets is the
provincial government's major task this year. Qinghai will
allocate 11 billion yuan in fixed-asset construction, with 5.52
billion yuan from the central government and 5.78 billion yuan
from local governments.
</P>
<P>
The province will continue a series of major projects funded by
the central government such as depth exploitation of Qinghai oil
field, completion of No.3 unit and operation of No.4 unit of
Lijiaxia hydro-station,
</P>
<P>
Emphasis will also be put on local government-funded projects
and infrastructure construction such as expansion work on the
Qinghai cement plant, Shitouxia hydro-station, Xining sewage
treatment plant, and projects like road-building and water supply.
</P>
<P>
Survey work of mineral resources has also started in Qinghai
Province with priority given to gold mines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
