<HEADLINE> Real Madrid Downs Borussia in First Leg of Champions Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 1 (Xinhua) -- In a delayed match, Real Madrid
scored two goals against nil to beat Borussia Dortmund in the
first leg of the European Champions Cup semifinals here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In the 24th minute, Fernando Morientes scored off a cross from
Brazilian Roberto Carlos to put the Spaniards ahead, his fourth
goal in the European competition.
</P>
<P>
The German side was forced to defense for the rest of the first
half while Real Madrid earned seven corners kicks, all turned into
vain to the relief of the Dortmund fans.
</P>
<P>
After the break, the Germans pushed for an equaliser but failed
to hit the target before Christian Karembeu sealed the competition
with his goal in the 67th minute.
</P>
<P>
The German side suffered the absence of internationals Jurgen
Kohler and Jorg Heinrich in the game delayed for more than one
hour due to a broken goal caused by the home fans. 
