<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Election Committee Subsector Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The following is a brief
introduction about the Election Committee Subsector Elections
being held Thursday in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) of China.
</P>
<P>
There are about 140,000 voters from 31 subsectors representing
various trades, professions, labor and social service sectors, and
district-based organizations. The voters are to choose their
representatives on the 800-strong Election Committee through the
subsector elections, part of the SAR's first Legislative Council
elections scheduled for May 24.
</P>
<P>
A total of 963 candidates will compete for 588 seats on the
Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
The 588 members, together with 95 members already returned from
four uncontested subsectors -- the Commercial (second), Hong Kong
Chinese Enterprises Association, the Industrial (second) and the
members of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, 77 ex-officio members including
Hong Kong deputies to the National People's Congress of China and
members of the Provisional Legislative Council, and 40
representatives nominated by the religious subsector, will form
the Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Election Committee will then elect 10 Legislative Council
members on May 24.
</P>
<P>
Under the Basic Law, the SAR's first Legislative Council will
be made up of 60 members. In addition to the 10 members to be
returned by the Election Committee, 20 will be elected in the
geographical constituencies through direct elections and 30 chosen
from the functional constituencies.
</P>
<P>
The term of the first Legislative Council, the legislature in
the SAR, shall be two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
