<HEADLINE> Beijing To Host Household Appliances Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A major international exhibition
of electric appliances for household use is scheduled for April
14-17 at the China International World Trade Center in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Companies from Germany, France, Italy, the Netherlands, China
and elsewhere will participate in the show, which is held every
two years.
</P>
<P>
Demand for household electric appliances in China's domestic
market is expected to grow ten percent this year, with rural areas
being a major growth sector.
</P>
<P>
Studies have found that, over the next three years, at least 70
percent of urban households will get new color TVs, refrigerators,
and washing machines to replace old ones. In addition, some seven
million young people get married each year and want to furnish
their new homes with new electric appliances.
</P>
<P>
China's 900 million people living in rural areas, whose living
standards keep improving, are also a major guarantee of robust
growth in the industry, experts say. 
</P>
