<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Juventus Beats Monaco in Champions Cup First Leg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Alessandro Del Piero scored a hat
trick including two penalties to pace Juventus for a 4-1 victory
over Monaco in the first leg semifinals of the European Champions
Cup in Turin on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the Delle Alpi stadium, Juventus, winners two season ago,
marked its return to top form with goals through Del Piero and
midfielder Zinedine Zidane.
</P>
<P>
Juventus that lost the title match to Borussia Dortmund last
season, opened the account in the 34th minute when Del Piero hit
the target from a free kick which slipped off the fingertip of
goalkeeper Fabien Barthez.
</P>
<P>
First half injury time brought two more goals in the space of a
minute.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Francisco Da Costa fired a low shot from a corner
kick for the Monaco equalizer before Del Piero put Juventus ahead
again with a power shot from the spot.
</P>
<P>
Del Piero then scored his second penalty in the 62nd minute
after Monaco defender Muhammaed Konjik pulled down Filippo Inzaghi.
</P>
<P>
Zidane sealed the game with a brilliant strike three minutes
from the end. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
