<HEADLINE> HK's Election Committee Subsector Elections Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Voting began on Thursday in the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) to choose 588
members of an 800-strong Election Committee which will elect 10
Legislative Council members on May 24.
</P>
<P>
Voters from 31 subsectors representing various trades,
professions, labor and social service sectors, and district-based
organizations began to cast their votes to choose their
representatives on the Election Committee through the Subsector
Elections.
</P>
<P>
Ninety polling stations across the SAR were opened at 7:30 a.m.
(local time) for about 140,000 voters, and voting of the polls,
part of the SAR's first Legislative Council elections scheduled
for May 24, will last until 10:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
A total of 588 members will be chosen from 963 candidates to
join others in forming the Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
The Election Committee will be made up of 95 members already
returned from four uncontested subsectors, 77 ex-officio members,
40 representatives nominated by the religious subsector, as well
as the 588 members.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law, the SAR's first Legislative Council
will be made up of 60 members. In addition to the 10 members to be
returned by the Election Committee on May 24, 20 will be elected
in the geographical constituencies through direct elections and 30
are to be chosen from the functional constituencies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
