<HEADLINE> French Centrist Party Expels 3 Regional Leaders for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- France's centrist Union for French
Democracy (UDF) announced Wednesday that it is expelling three
regional leaders who allied with the far-right National Front (FN)
in the regional elections in mid-March.
</P>
<P>
UDF president Francois Leotard said the three are the president
of regional council of Rhone-Alpes Charles Millon, that of the
northern region of Picardie millionaire Charles Baur, and that of
the French Catalonian region of Languedoc-Rousillon Jacques Blanc.
</P>
<P>
The three were among the six UDF politicians who allied with FN
in order to be reelected the council presidents of their regions
on March 20.
</P>
<P>
The other three were forced to resign under tremendous pressure
from both the right and left political circles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
